data.chText: 多才多艺的；有多种技能的；多面手的
data.enText: able to do many different things

data.chText: 他是个多才多艺的演员，扮演过各种各样的角色。
data.enText: He's a versatile actor who has played a wide variety of parts.

data.chText: 鸡蛋容易烹煮，怎么做着吃都行。
data.enText: Eggs are easy to cook and are an extremely versatile food.

data.chText: 她是位特别多才多艺的设计师。
data.enText: She is a designer of extraordinary versatility.

simple_means.memory_skill: vers 转 + atile → 玩得转 → 多才的

tr: able to move freely in all directions
example: an owl's versatile toe can move backward and forward
an insect's versatile antennae can move up and down or laterally
a versatile anther of a flower moves freely in the wind

tr: competent in many areas and able to turn with ease from one thing to another

value.def: If you say that a person is versatile, you approve of them because they have many different skills.

example.ex: He had been one of the game's most versatile athletes.
example.tran: 他是这项运动中技术最全面的运动员之一。

value.tran: 有多种技能的;多才多艺的

example.ex: Aileen stands out for her incredible versatility as an actress.
example.tran: 艾琳多才多艺，是一位出类拔萃的女演员。

value.def: A tool, machine, or material that is versatile can be used for many different purposes.

example.ex: Never before has computing been so versatile.
example.tran: 计算机的用途从没像现在这么广泛过。

value.tran: 有多种用途的;多功能的

example.ex: Velvet is not known for its versatility.
example.tran: 天鹅绒的用途并不是非常广泛。
